Avoiding low-quality images or NSFW content can be described using natural language
query = {"yellow handbag":1.0, "lowres, blurry, low quality":-1.1}
In the example below the initial results contain three  low-quality images. These are denoted by a red mark.

Searching with images alone can also be performed to  utilize image similarity to find similar looking items.
query = {image_url:1.0}
It can also be easily extended in the same way as with text to include multiple multimodal terms.
query = {image_url:1.0, "RED":1.0}

An example query with additional prompting is below:

query = {"cozy sweater, xmas, festive, holidays":1.0}

The impact of this prompting on the results can be seen in the animation.

